  <center><img src=/news/mar22/xdead.jpg></center><br><br>
<center>Rumors have abounded of a big breasted lawn fairy defeating all 
attempts to remove her and her regime from power in the plane of air. 
Today, after several weeks of preparation and covert intelligence 
missions, the Fury's Edge coalition amassed in Xegony's backyard and 
removed her and her cohorts from power. In what was a culmination of 
months of teamwork and practicing together as a precise machine of 
cohesive destruction, Xegony was finally bested for the first time on 
Morell Thule.
<br><br>
The following loots were awarded to Ceri, Solthan (Mr. Pinkie) and 
Tegamyen respectively.
<br><br>
<img src=/news/mar22/xloot2.jpg><br>
<img src=/news/mar22/xloot1.jpg><br>
<img src=/news/mar22/xloot3.jpg><br>
<br><br>
On a more serious note, over the past several weeks, we've had our ups 
and downs, mostly downs it's felt like. On days like today however, I am 
forced to step back and really appreciate the guild that I am 
priviledged to help lead with Solthan and our crack team of officers. I 
continue to play the game due the people that bear the Fury's Edge 
guildtag, even tho 75% of the time Solthan and I want to punt most of 
the guild into the next MMORPG and be done with it. I'd like to say hats 
off to everyone in FE for your hardwork and dedication to a game that 
has lost some of the appeal it had when we originally started playing. 
Only two to go and one of those is very near his demise as well!!
<br><br><img src=/news/mar22/xshield.jpg></center>
